com.parrot.arsdk.arcommands

Class ARCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.parrot.arsdk.arsal.ARNativeData
      • com.parrot.arsdk.arcommands.ARCommand

  • public class ARCommand
extends ARNativeData
    Java representation of a C ARCommand object.
    This class holds either app-generated objects, that are to be sent to the device, or network-generated objects, that are to be decoded by the application.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      ARCommand()
      Creates a new, empty ARCommand with the default size.
      This is a typical constructor for app-generated ARCommand.
      To optimize memory, the application can reuse an ARCommand object after it was disposed.
      ARCommand(ARNativeData oldData)
      Creates a new ARCommand from another ARNativeData instance.
      This is a typical constructor for network-generated ARCommand.
      To optimize memory, the application can reuse an ARCommand object after it was disposed.
      ARCommand(ARNativeData oldData, int capacity)
      Creates a new ARCommand from another ARNativeData, with a given minimum capacity.
      This is a typical constructor for network-generated ARCommand.
      To optimize memory, the application can reuse an ARCommand object after it was disposed.
      ARCommand(int capacity)
      Creates a new, empty ARCommand with an user-specified size.
      This is a typical constructor for app-generated ARCommand.
      To optimize memory, the application can reuse an ARCommand object after it was disposed.
      ARCommand(long data, int dataSize)
      Creates a new ARCommand from a c pointer and size.
      To optimize memory, the application can reuse an ARCommand object after it was disposed.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR_ENUM decode()
      Decodes the current ARCommand, calling commands listeners
      If a listener was set for the Class/Command contained within the ARCommand, its onClassCommandUpdate(...) function will be called in the current thread.
      ARCOMMANDS_GENERATOR_ERROR_ENUM setARDrone3AnimationsFlip(ARCOMMANDS_ARDRONE3_ANIMATIONS_FLIP_DIRECTION_ENUM direction)

      All ARDrone3-only commands

      • decode

        public ARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR_ENUM decode()
        Decodes the current ARCommand, calling commands listeners
        If a listener was set for the Class/Command contained within the ARCommand, its onClassCommandUpdate(...) function will be called in the current thread.
        Returns:
        An ARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR_ENUM error code

      • setARDrone3PilotingPCMD

        public ARCOMMANDS_GENERATOR_ERROR_ENUM setARDrone3PilotingPCMD(byte flag,
                                                      byte roll,
                                                      byte pitch,
                                                      byte yaw,
                                                      byte gaz,
                                                      float psi)
        Set an ARCommand to hold the command PCMD of class Piloting in project ARDrone3

        Project ARDrone3 description:
        All ARDrone3-only commands

        Class Piloting description:
        All commands related to piloting the totoDrone

        Command PCMD description:
        Ask the drone to move around.

        This function reuses the current ARCommand, replacing its content with a new command created from the current params
        Parameters:
        _flag - Boolean flag to activate roll/pitch movement
        _roll - Roll consign for the drone [-100;100]
        _pitch - Pitch consign for the drone [-100;100]
        _yaw - Yaw consign for the drone [-100;100]
        _gaz - Gaz consign for the drone [-100;100]
        _psi - Magnetic north heading of the controlling device (deg) [-180;180]
        Returns:
        An ARCOMMANDS_GENERATOR_ERROR_ENUM error code.

        Ask the drone to move camera

        Command Orientation description:
        Ask the drone to move camera.

        This function reuses the current ARCommand, replacing its content with a new command created from the current params
        Parameters:
        _tilt - Tilt camera consign for the drone (in degree)
        _tilt - The value is saturated by the drone.
        _tilt - Saturation value is sent by thre drone through CameraSettingsChanged command.
        _pan - Pan camera consign for the drone (in degree)
        _pan - The value is saturated by the drone.
        _pan - Saturation value is sent by thre drone through CameraSettingsChanged command.
        Returns:
        An ARCOMMANDS_GENERATOR_ERROR_ENUM error code.
